HEADWORD: molality
<hw>molality</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A measure of
concentaration of substances in mixtures, 1 molal being the
concentration of a solution containing 1 mole of solute per 1000 grams
of solvent. Compare <er>molar</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

